trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of key/value pairs that are organized based on the hash code of the key.
trans-unit.target: 表示根据键的哈希代码进行组织的键/值对的集合。

trans-unit.source: Each element is a key/value pair stored in a <xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry> object.
trans-unit.target: 每个元素是存储在一个键/值对<xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry>对象。

trans-unit.source: A key cannot be `null`, but a value can be.
trans-unit.target: 密钥不能为`null`，但可以是一个值。

trans-unit.source: The objects used as keys by a <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> are required to override the <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method (or the <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider> interface) and the <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method (or the <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> interface).
trans-unit.target: 用作键，即可通过对象<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>需重写<xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法 (或<xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider>接口) 和<xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法 (或<xref:System.Collections.IComparer>接口)。

trans-unit.source: The implementation of both methods and interfaces must handle case sensitivity the same way; otherwise, the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> might behave incorrectly.
trans-unit.target: 方法和接口的实现必须处理区分大小写相同的方式;否则为<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>可能出现错误的行为。

trans-unit.source: For example, when creating a <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>, you must use the <xref:System.Collections.CaseInsensitiveHashCodeProvider> class (or any case-insensitive <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider> implementation) with the <xref:System.Collections.CaseInsensitiveComparer> class (or any case-insensitive <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> implementation).
trans-unit.target: 例如，在创建<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>，必须使用<xref:System.Collections.CaseInsensitiveHashCodeProvider>类 (或任何不区分大小写<xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider>实现) 使用<xref:System.Collections.CaseInsensitiveComparer>类 (或任何不区分大小写<xref:System.Collections.IComparer>实现)。

trans-unit.source: Furthermore, these methods must produce the same results when called with the same parameters while the key exists in the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>.
trans-unit.target: 此外，这些方法必须生成相同的结果中存在的键时使用相同的参数调用时<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>。

trans-unit.source: An alternative is to use a <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> constructor with an <xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer> parameter.
trans-unit.target: 一种替代方法是使用<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>具有构造函数<xref:System.Collections.IEqualityComparer>参数。

trans-unit.source: If key equality were simply reference equality, the inherited implementation of <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> would suffice.
trans-unit.target: 如果键相等性只需引用相等性的继承的实现<xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>和<xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>便已足够。

trans-unit.source: Key objects must be immutable as long as they are used as keys in the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>.
trans-unit.target: 密钥对象必须是不可变，只要它们是否用作中的键<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>。

trans-unit.source: When an element is added to the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>, the element is placed into a bucket based on the hash code of the key.
trans-unit.target: 当将元素添加到<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>，该元素放入存储桶基于键的哈希代码。

trans-unit.source: Subsequent lookups of the key use the hash code of the key to search in only one particular bucket, thus substantially reducing the number of key comparisons required to find an element.
trans-unit.target: 密钥的后续查找使用密钥的哈希代码要搜索中只有一个特定的存储桶，这将大大减少查找元素所需的键比较的次数。

trans-unit.source: The load factor of a <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> determines the maximum ratio of elements to buckets.
trans-unit.target: 已加载因子<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>确定元素与存储桶的最大比率。

trans-unit.source: Smaller load factors cause faster average lookup times at the cost of increased memory consumption.
trans-unit.target: 较小负载因素会导致更快地平均查找时间，但代价是增加的内存消耗。

trans-unit.source: The default load factor of 1.0 generally provides the best balance between speed and size.
trans-unit.target: 1.0 默认负载因子通常提供速度和大小之间的最佳平衡。

trans-unit.source: A different load factor can also be specified when the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> is created.
trans-unit.target: 也可以是不同的负载因素时指定<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>创建。

trans-unit.source: As elements are added to a <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>, the actual load factor of the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> increases.
trans-unit.target: 如元素添加到<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>的实际加载因子<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>会增加。

trans-unit.source: When the actual load factor reaches the specified load factor, the number of buckets in the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> is automatically increased to the smallest prime number that is larger than twice the current number of <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> buckets.
trans-unit.target: 在实际加载因子到达指定的负载因子中的存储桶的数量<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>自动增加到大于当前数的两倍最小质数<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>存储桶。

trans-unit.source: Each key object in the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> must provide its own hash function, which can be accessed by calling <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable.GetHash%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 在每个键对象<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>必须提供其自己的哈希函数，可通过调用访问<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable.GetHash%2A>。

trans-unit.source: However, any object implementing <xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider> can be passed to a <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> constructor, and that hash function is used for all objects in the table.
trans-unit.target: 但是，任何对象实现<xref:System.Collections.IHashCodeProvider>可以传递给<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>构造函数，并且哈希函数用于表中的所有对象。

trans-unit.source: The capacity of a <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> is the number of elements the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> can hold.
trans-unit.target: 容量<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>是元素的数目<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>可以保存。

trans-unit.source: As elements are added to a <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>, the capacity is automatically increased as required through reallocation.
trans-unit.target: 如元素添加到<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>，自动增加容量通过重新分配所需的方式。

trans-unit.source: For very large <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> objects, you can increase the maximum capacity to 2 billion elements on a 64-bit system by setting the `enabled` attribute of the configuration element to `true` in the run-time environment.
trans-unit.target: 对于非常大<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>对象，你可以通过设置增加到 20 亿元素在 64 位系统上的最大容量`enabled`到的配置元素的属性`true`在运行时环境中。

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`For Each` in Visual Basic) returns an object of the type of the elements in the collection.
trans-unit.target: `foreach` C# 语言的语句 (`For Each`在 Visual Basic 中) 返回集合中的元素的类型的对象。

trans-unit.source: Since each element of the <xref:System.Collections.Hashtable> is a key/value pair, the element type is not the type of the key or the type of the value.
trans-unit.target: 由于每个元素的<xref:System.Collections.Hashtable>是一个键/值对，元素类型不是键的类型或值的类型。

trans-unit.source: Instead, the element type is <xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry>.
trans-unit.target: 相反，元素类型是<xref:System.Collections.DictionaryEntry>。

trans-unit.source: <see cref="T:System.Collections.Hashtable" /> is thread safe for use by multiple reader threads and a single writing thread.
trans-unit.target: <see cref="T:System.Collections.Hashtable" /> 是线程安全的由多个读取器线程和单个写入线程使用。

trans-unit.source: It is thread safe for multi-thread use when only one of the threads perform write (update) operations, which allows for lock-free reads provided that the writers are serialized to the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Hashtable" />.
trans-unit.target: 它不是线程安全多线程使用时，只有一个线程执行写入 （更新） 操作，从而允许进行无锁读取，前提是编写器序列化为<see cref="T:System.Collections.Hashtable" />。

trans-unit.source: To support multiple writers all operations on the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Hashtable" /> must be done through the wrapper returned by the <see cref="M:System.Collections.Hashtable.Synchronized(System.Collections.Hashtable)" /> method, provided that there are no threads reading the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Hashtable" /> object.
trans-unit.target: 若要支持上的多个编写器的所有操作<see cref="T:System.Collections.Hashtable" />必须通过返回的包装器来完成<see cref="M:System.Collections.Hashtable.Synchronized(System.Collections.Hashtable)" />方法，提供有读取无线程<see cref="T:System.Collections.Hashtable" />对象。

trans-unit.source: Enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 枚举整个集合本质上不是线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads can still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: 即使某个集合已同步，其他线程仍可以修改该集合，这会导致枚举数引发异常。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举期间锁定集合，或者捕获由其他线程进行的更改所导致的异常。

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of the enumerators.
trans-unit.target: C# 语言的 `foreach` 语句（在 Visual Basic 中为 `for each`）隐藏了枚举数的复杂性。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: 因此，建议使用 `foreach`，而不是直接操作枚举数。

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: 枚举器可用于读取集合中的数据，但不能用于修改基础集合。

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 最初，枚举数定位在集合中第一个元素的前面。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 也会将枚举器放回此位置。

trans-unit.source: At this position, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 在此位置上，未定义 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 因此，在读取 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 的值之前，必须调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 将枚举器向前移动到集合的第一个元素。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: 在调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 或 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 之前，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 返回同一对象。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 将 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 设置为下一个元素。

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: 如果<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>越过的末尾的集合，枚举数定位在集合中的最后一个元素的后面和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: 当枚举器位于此位置上，后续调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>还返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果最后一次调用到<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 若要再次将 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 设置为集合的第一个元素，可以调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 并接着调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>。

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 只要集合保持不变，枚举数就保持有效。

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and its behavior is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果对集合进行更改（如添加、修改或删除元素），则枚举数将失效且不可恢复，而且其行为是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 该枚举数不具有独占访问集合的权限；因此，枚举整个集合本质上不是一个线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can lock the collection during the entire enumeration.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举过程中锁定集合。

trans-unit.source: To allow the collection to be accessed by multiple threads for reading and writing, you must implement your own synchronization.
trans-unit.target: 若要允许多个线程访问集合以进行读写操作，则必须实现自己的同步。

trans-unit.source: An <see cref="T:System.Collections.IEnumerator" /> that can be used to iterate through the collection.

trans-unit.source: [Visual Basic, C#]
trans-unit.target: [Visual Basic、 C#]

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of the enumerators.
trans-unit.target: C# 语言的 `foreach` 语句（在 Visual Basic 中为 `for each`）隐藏了枚举数的复杂性。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: 因此，建议使用 `foreach`，而不是直接操作枚举数。

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: 枚举器可用于读取集合中的数据，但不能用于修改基础集合。

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 最初，枚举数定位在集合中第一个元素的前面。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 也会将枚举器放回此位置。

trans-unit.source: At this position, calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: 在此位置，调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>引发异常。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 因此，在读取 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 的值之前，必须调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 将枚举器向前移动到集合的第一个元素。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: 在调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 或 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 之前，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 返回同一对象。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 将 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 设置为下一个元素。

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: 如果<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>越过的末尾的集合，枚举数定位在集合中的最后一个元素的后面和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: 当枚举器位于此位置上，后续调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>还返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: 如果最后一次调用到<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`，则调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>引发异常。

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 若要再次将 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 设置为集合的第一个元素，可以调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 并接着调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>。

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 只要集合保持不变，枚举数就保持有效。

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator can be invalidated and the next call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> throws an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.
trans-unit.target: 如果对集合进行更改，例如添加、 修改或删除元素，枚举数将失效，并且下次调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>或<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>引发<xref:System.InvalidOperationException>。

trans-unit.source: If the collection is modified between <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the element that it is set to, even if the enumerator is already invalidated.
trans-unit.target: 如果之间修改集合<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>返回到，设置的元素，即使枚举数已经无效。

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 该枚举数不具有独占访问集合的权限；因此，枚举整个集合本质上不是一个线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads can still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: 即使某个集合已同步，其他线程仍可以修改该集合，这会导致枚举数引发异常。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举期间锁定集合，或者捕获由其他线程进行的更改所导致的异常。
